                <Header>Disclosures</Header>
                <Paragraph>Strict rules govern the conduct of executive branch appointees and require every appointee in an executive branch agency to sign an ethics pledge. A waiver is permitted in cases where the literal application of the pledge is inconsistent with its purposes or is not in the public interest. Waivers that have been granted are posted online.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
